1e:["$","article",null,{"style":{"padding":"4rem 0"},"children":["$","div",null,{"style":{"maxWidth":900,"margin":"0 auto","padding":"0 1.5rem"},"children":[["$","div",null,{"style":{"position":"relative","width":"100%","height":"400px","borderRadius":"12px","overflow":"hidden","marginBottom":"2rem"},"children":["$","$L2a",null,{"src":"/images/img11.jpeg","alt":"Custom composite deck installation in Northern Virginia — Trex Transcend in Havana Gold","fill":true,"style":{"objectFit":"cover"},"sizes":"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px","priority":true}]}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"marginBottom":"1rem","lineHeight":1.7},"children":"If you're researching composite decking prices in Loudoun County, Fairfax County, or Prince William County, you've probably noticed that most online cost guides give national averages that are wildly off for our market. A HomeAdvisor estimate of “$22 per square foot” has no connection to what a licensed Northern Virginia contractor will actually charge you."}],["$","p",null,{"style":"$1e:props:children:props:children:1:props:style","children":"This guide uses our own project data from 2024–2026 builds across Ashburn, Leesburg, Reston, McLean, Centreville, and Manassas. Every number below reflects what homeowners in this market actually paid — materials, labor, permits, railings, and cleanup included."}],["$","h2",null,{"style":{"fontSize":"1.8rem","fontWeight":700,"marginBottom":"1.5rem"},"children":"Composite Deck Cost by Brand (Installed)"}],["$","p",null,{"style":"$1e:props:children:props:children:1:props:style","children":"The brand and product line you choose is the single biggest factor in your final price. Here's what each major composite manufacturer costs per square foot when professionally installed in Northern Virginia:"}],["$","div",null,{"style":{"overflowX":"auto","marginBottom":"2rem"},"children":["$","table",null,{"style":{"width":"100%","borderCollapse":"collapse","fontSize":"0.9rem"},"children":[["$","thead",null,{"children":[