37:["$","h2",null,{"style":"$1e:props:children:props:children:3:props:style","children":"Trex Decking Cost Breakdown (Our #1 Installed Brand)"}]
38:["$","p",null,{"style":"$1e:props:children:props:children:1:props:style","children":["As a ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"Trex Platinum Partner"}]," — a designation held by fewer than 1% of deck builders nationally — we install more Trex than any other brand. Here's how the three main Trex lines compare for Northern Virginia homeowners:"]}]
39:["$","h3",null,{"style":{"fontSize":"1.2rem","fontWeight":600,"margin":"1.5rem 0 0.5rem"},"children":"Trex Enhance ($30–$48/sqft installed)"}]
3a:["$","p",null,{"style":"$1e:props:children:props:children:1:props:style","children":["The entry point into Trex composite. The Basics line offers solid, uniform colors while Naturals adds multi-tonal wood grain streaking. Both feature Trex's shell protection for fade, stain, and mold resistance. Best for homeowners who want composite durability at the closest price point to wood. Typical full project (300 sqft deck + aluminum railing + 4-step stair): ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"$$18,000–$24,000"}],"."]}]
3b:["$","h3",null,{"style":"$39:props:style","children":"Trex Transcend ($45–$65/sqft installed)"}]
3c:["$","p",null,{"style":"$1e:props:children:props:children:1:props:style","children":["Our most-installed product line. Transcend boards have a deeper, more realistic wood grain and the thickest protective shell in the Trex lineup. The color palette — Havana Gold, Spiced Rum, Island Mist, Lava Rock — is specifically designed to complement Virginia's red brick and stone colonial architecture. Typical full project (350 sqft + Trex Signature railing + multi-step stair): ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"$$28,000–$38,000"}],"."]}]
3d:["$","h3",null,{"style":"$39:props:style","children":"Trex Transcend Lineage ($50–$65/sqft installed)"}]
3e:["$","p",null,{"style":"$1e:props:children:props:children:1:props:style","children":["Trex's newest premium tier, launched in 2024. Lineage features the most realistic wood grain ever produced in composite — you genuinely cannot tell it from hardwood without touching it. Backed by a 50-year fade and stain warranty. Typical full project (400 sqft + Trex Signature railing + lighting): ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"$$35,000–$48,000"}],"."]}]
3f:["$","h2",null,{"style":{"fontSize":"1.8rem","fontWeight":700,"marginBottom":"1.5rem","marginTop":"2.5rem"},"children":"TimberTech & AZEK Cost Breakdown"}]
40:["$","p",null,{"style":"$1e:props:children:props:children:1:props:style","children":["TimberTech and AZEK are manufactured by the same parent company (AZEK Building Products). TimberTech composites use a wood-plastic composite core, while AZEK uses a full polymer (PVC) core — no wood content at all. As a ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"TimberTech Certified Installer"}],", we offer their full product range."]}]
41:["$","h3",null,{"style":"$39:props:style","children":"TimberTech Pro & Edge ($40–$60/sqft installed)"}]
42:["$","p",null,{"style":"$1e:props:children:props:children:1:props:style","children":["Direct competitors to Trex Transcend. TimberTech's polymer cap is approximately 35% thicker than Trex's, which some contractors argue delivers better long-term scratch resistance. The Edge Prime+ line features a distinctive wide-plank look (5.5” boards) that photographs beautifully. Typical full project (300 sqft + composite railing): ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"$$22,000–$32,000"}],"."]}]
43:["$","h3",null,{"style":"$39:props:style","children":"TimberTech AZEK ($50–$75/sqft installed)"}]
44:["$","p",null,{"style":"$1e:props:children:props:children:1:props:style","children":["The premium tier — full PVC with zero wood content. AZEK boards are virtually impervious to moisture, will not swell or contract, and carry a 50-year warranty. The Vintage collection (Mahogany, English Walnut, Coastline) delivers the deepest color saturation in the industry. Ideal for pool decks, waterfront properties, and homeowners who want the absolute best regardless of budget. Typical full project (400 sqft + AZEK railing + stair lighting): ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"$$38,000–$55,000"}],"."]}]
